---
id: org.dxos.plugin.trello
name: TrelloPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Trello board and card sync for Composer. Reads boards/lists/cards via the Trello
REST API, writes them as `TrelloBoard` and `TrelloCard` ECHO objects, and views
them through the existing Kanban plugin.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |

## Types

```mdl
type Label
  fields:
    trelloId: string
    name?: string
    color?: string         # red | yellow | green | blue | orange | purple | pink | sky | lime | black
```

```mdl
type Member
  fields:
    trelloId: string
    username?: string
    fullName?: string
    avatarUrl?: string
```

```mdl
type TrelloCard
  meta:
    keys: [{ source: 'trello.com', id: trelloCardId }]
  fields:
    name: string
    description?: string
    board?: ref<TrelloBoard>
    trelloListId: string
    listName?: string
    position?: number
    dueDate?: string                 # ISO timestamp
    dueComplete?: boolean
    url?: string                     # https://trello.com/c/...
    closed?: boolean
    lastActivityAt?: string
    labels?: Label[]
    members?: Member[]
```

```mdl
type TrelloBoard
  meta:
    keys: [{ source: 'trello.com', id: trelloBoardId }]
  fields:
    name: string
    url?: string
    accessToken?: ref<AccessToken>   # Trello API key + token; see service below
    kanbanId?: string                # Id of the Kanban view rendered for this board
    pollIntervalMs?: number          # advisory; sync is currently manual
```

## Services

```mdl
service TrelloCredentials
  desc: Effect Layer that resolves the Trello {apiKey, apiToken} pair from a board's AccessToken ref. Modeled on plugin-mailbox's GoogleCredentials.
  ops:
    fromBoard(boardRef): Layer<TrelloCredentials>
    get(): Effect<TrelloAuth, Error>
```

## Operations

```mdl
op SyncBoard
  desc: Pulls boards/lists/cards from Trello and reconciles them with ECHO. Idempotent on Obj.Meta.keys.
  input:
    board: ref<TrelloBoard>
  output:
    cardsCreated: number
    cardsUpdated: number
    cardsClosed: number
```

```mdl
op PushCard
  desc: Pushes a single TrelloCard's name/description back to Trello via the REST API.
  input:
    board: ref<TrelloBoard>
    card: ref<TrelloCard>
  output:
    pushed: boolean
```

## Components

```mdl
component TrelloCardArticle
  desc: Article-shaped editor for a TrelloCard. Read/write fields (name, description) plus read-only computed fields (listName, dueDate, members) plus a "Push to Trello" toolbar action.
  props:
    subject: TrelloCard
    role?: string
    attendableId?: string
```

```mdl
component TrelloCard
  desc: Inline card-content renderer used by Kanban tiles and search hits. Title + listName + open-in-Trello link.
  props:
    card: TrelloCard
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Board sync
  req F-1.1: SyncBoard reconciles cards by Obj.Meta.keys[source='trello.com'] — never by sequence position.
  req F-1.2: Cards absent from the remote board are marked closed (not deleted).
  req F-1.3: Reconciliation is scoped to the board being synced; it never touches cards owned by another board.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Card push
  req F-2.1: PushCard targets the card's owning board (via `card.board` ref) — never picks an unrelated board with credentials.
  req F-2.2: PushCard surfaces success/failure via the operation invoker's toast pipeline.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Native Kanban view
  req F-3.1: A TrelloBoard renders as a Kanban view via plugin-kanban — no custom board-level UI in plugin-trello.
  req F-3.2: TrelloCard contributes a `card--content` surface so Kanban tiles can render Trello specifics (list, link).
  req F-3.3: TrelloCard contributes `article` and `section` surfaces for the planks/sidebars.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: idempotent sync
  given: a board with N cards already synced
  then: re-running SyncBoard creates 0, updates 0, and closes 0 cards
```

```mdl
test T-2: scoped reconciliation
  given: two boards A and B in the same space, and SyncBoard is invoked on board A
  then: cards owned by board B are unchanged regardless of A's remote response
```

```mdl
test T-3: kanban renders trello cards
  given: a TrelloBoard with a Kanban view and TrelloCards attached
  then: each card tile is rendered by the TrelloCard `card--content` surface
```

## Roadmap (out of scope for the initial PR)

See `DESIGN.md` for the proposed evolution to a generic `Sync` object that can
factor out into a core plugin so other connectors (Linear, GitHub) can reuse the
mechanics.

```mdl
feat F-4: Generic Sync object [planned]
  req F-4.1: Define a `Sync` ECHO type with { endpoint, kanban: ref<Kanban>, lastSyncAt }; one Sync per connected board.
  req F-4.2: Move sync scheduling + auth resolution out of plugin-trello into a shared `plugin-sync` (or core) so plugin-trello becomes a pure mapper.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Two-way labels [planned]
  req F-5.1: Map Trello labels to Composer Tags using the cross-cutting Tag ontology (open issue tracked separately).
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Read-only fields via Form [planned]
  req F-6.1: Migrate TrelloCardArticle to `@dxos/react-ui-form`'s Form component; add a "computed/read-only" annotation for fields like listName, dueDate, members.
```
